Name
       zoomTo - Zooms in the viewable window to the point defined by the coor-
       dinates with a default radius of 150 microns

Syntax
       zoomTo

       [-help]

       x y

       [-radius <value>]

       Zooms  in  the  viewable window to the point defined by the coordinates
       with a default radius of 150 microns.

       You can also use the Select bar to specify the zoom area center and ra-
       dius directly from the GUI.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each zoomTo parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man zoomTo.

       -radius <value>
              Zooms in the viewable window to a radius of the specified  value
              in  microns,  with  the center at the point specified by <x> and
              <y>. The radius <value> is of type float.

              Default: 150 microns

       <x y>  Zooms in the viewable window to the point defined by the coordi-
              nates, x and y.

Examples
              * When the following command is run, the display zooms in to the
                point with x=100 and y=200. The display area  is  centered  at
                this point and has the default radius of 150 microns:

                zoomTo 100 200

              * When  the  following  command  is run, the display zooms in to
                point with x=100 and y=200. The display area  is  centered  at
                this point and has a radius of 50 microns:

                zoomTo 100 200 -radius 50

